In this paper, we report &lt;b>MaginotDNS&lt;/b>, a powerful cache poisoning attack against DNS servers that simultaneously act as recursive resolvers and forwarders (termed as &lt;i>CDNS&lt;/i>).
&lt;br>&lt;/br>
MaginotDNS: &lt;a href="https://maginotdns.net/">https://maginotdns.net/&lt;/a>
&lt;h2>CVEs (9 in total)&lt;/h2>
&lt;li>Knot Resolver: &lt;a href="https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2022-30250">CVE-2022-30250&lt;/a>, &lt;a href="https://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2022-30251">CVE-2022-30251&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
